## Dimension: Non-Redundancy

**Definition**: The degree to which claims are semantically distinct without unnecessary duplication.

**Why This Matters**: Redundant claims waste expert attention in Delphi rounds and obscure the actual diversity of perspectives. However, apparent similarity may reflect real nuance—preserve genuine differences.

